This paper deals with Seq2Seq models, which are commonly used in natural language processing tasks, suggesting that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the model's ability to generalize, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Learning). The paper uses neural networks, which is a common technique in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the sensitivity of the model, which is a topic that falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses a simple symbol rewriting task, which could potentially fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
